      "title": "Results and Interpretations ",
      "cols": [
        "Finding / Observation (Structure/Region)",
        "Description (Normal or Potential Abnormality)",
        "General Interpretation / Significance"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "Normal",
          "Symmetrical brain & optic nerves",
          "No action needed"
        ],
        [
          "T2 bright lesion",
          "Oval lesion in white matter",
          "May suggest demyelination; neurologist referral"
        ],
        [
          "Enhancing mass",
          "Nodular uptake in orbit",
          "Biopsy or oncology consult"
        ],
        [
          "Optic nerve thickening",
          "Contrast enhancement along nerve",
          "Optic neuritis; steroid therapy"
        ],
        [
          "Orbital Soft Tissues / Globes",
          "No discrete orbital mass or fluid collection. Globes appear intact and normal.",
          "Normal orbital contents. Pathologies may include tumors (e.g., lymphoma, metastases), cellulitis, pseudotumor, vascular lesions, or intraocular abnormalities."
        ],
        [
          "Contrast Enhancement (if used)",
          "No abnormal contrast enhancement seen in brain or orbits.",
          "Normal blood-brain and blood-eye barriers. Abnormal enhancement can indicate inflammation, infection, tumor, or active lesions (e.g., MS, abscess)."
        ],
        [
          "Paranasal Sinuses / Mastoids",
          "Paranasal sinuses and mastoid air cells are clear.",
          "Incidental findings. Sinusitis, mastoiditis, or fluid levels may be seen even if unrelated to the primary concern. Important for headaches or orbital pain workup."
        ]
      ]
    },
    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Brain + Orbits painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may hear loud knocking sounds, but the scan itself is painless.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does the scan take?",
        "answer": "20–40 minutes depending on contrast use and patient cooperation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need contrast?",
        "answer": "Your doctor decides based on symptoms. Tumours, infections, or inflammation cases usually require it.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "Yes, unless your slot includes contrast and you were specifically asked to fast.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is it safe for kids?",
        "answer": "Absolutely. We use paediatric protocols and have experienced technologists for children above 3 years.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRI Brain + Orbits cost at Cadabams Diagnostics?",
        "answer": "The \"MRI brain and orbits cost\" (SK5) can vary based on several factors, including the specifics of the procedure (e.g., use of contrast), and your insurance coverage. For detailed information on the cost of an **MRI Brain + Orbits** scan at Cadabams Diagnostics, insurance coverage, and any available payment options, please contact Cadabams Diagnostics directly. Our team will be happy to assist you."
      }
    ],
