    "markdown": "## MRI Brain + Orbits Overview\n\n### What This Combined Scan Covers\n- \\*\\*Brain parenchyma\\*\\* – grey and white matter, blood vessels\n- \\*\\*Orbits\\*\\* – eyeballs, optic nerves, muscles, fat, bony walls\n- \\*\\*Pituitary gland & cavernous sinus\\*\\* – hormone control and drainage areas\n### Why Choose Cadabams Diagnostics\n- \\*\\*3T MRI\\*\\* for crisp detail\n- \\*\\*Same-day & weekend slots\\*\\*\n- \\*\\*Radiologists with subspecialty training in neuro & orbit imaging\\*\\*\n- \\*\\*Transparent pricing & digital reports within 24 hours\\*\\*\n\n## Risks & Limitations of the MRI Brain + Orbits\n\n### MRI Safety Considerations\n- \\*\\*No ionising radiation\\*\\* – safe for repeated imaging\n- \\*\\*Contra-indications\\*\\*: non-MRI-safe pacemakers, certain aneurysm clips, cochlear implants\n- \\*\\*Contrast (gadolinium)\\*\\*: rare allergy risk; kidney function checked first\n### Claustrophobia and Contrast Limitations\n- Wide-bore 70 cm magnet and \\*\\*in-bore lighting\\*\\* reduce anxiety\n- Mild \\*\\*oral sedation\\*\\* available on request\n- Breast-feeding mothers can resume feeding after 24 h post-contrast\n\n## List of Parameters Considered During the MRI Brain + Orbits\n\n### Brain Parenchyma Evaluation\n- Grey–white matter differentiation\n- Ventricle size, midline shift\n- Micro-haemorrhages & white-matter lesions\n### Optic Nerves, Globe, Extra-Ocular Muscles\n- Nerve sheath thickness & enhancement\n- Globe contour, lens position, retinal detachment\n- Muscle swelling in thyroid eye disease\n### Pituitary, Cavernous Sinus, Orbital Apex\n- Pituitary height & stalk deviation\n- Cavernous sinus invasion by tumours\n- Superior orbital fissure crowding\n\n## When to Take Test\n\n- \\*\\*Unexplained headaches\\*\\* with visual symptoms\n- \\*\\*Trauma\\*\\* to face or skull base\n- \\*\\*Suspected tumours\\*\\* – meningioma, glioma, optic-nerve glioma\n- \\*\\*Infections\\*\\* – abscess, fungal sinusitis extending into orbit\n- \\*\\*Autoimmune & demyelination\\*\\* – multiple sclerosis, neuromyelitis optica\n\n## Benefits of Taking the Test\n\n- \\*\\*Non-invasive\\*\\* procedure – no needles unless contrast required\n- \\*\\*Zero radiation\\*\\* – ideal for children & follow-ups\n- \\*\\*High-resolution soft-tissue contrast\\*\\* – detects 1–2 mm lesions\n- \\*\\*Early detection\\*\\* – timely treatment protects vision & brain function\n\n## Illnesses Diagnosed with MRI Brain + Orbits\n\n| Condition | Key MRI Finding |\n|---|---|\n| \\*\\*Brain tumours\\*\\* | Enhancing mass with or without oedema |\n| \\*\\*Stroke\\*\\* | Restricted diffusion in acute phase |\n| \\*\\*Optic neuritis\\*\\* | T2 bright optic nerve with contrast uptake |\n| \\*\\*Orbital masses\\*\\* | Well-defined or infiltrative lesions |\n| \\*\\*Thyroid eye disease\\*\\* | Enlarged, T2-bright extra-ocular muscles |\n\n## Preparing for MRI Brain + Orbits\n\n### Instructions: Fasting, Clothing, Metal Objects\n- \\*\\*Fasting\\*\\*: 4 hours only if contrast planned; water allowed\n- \\*\\*Clothing\\*\\*: wear cotton, no zips or sequins; locker provided\n- \\*\\*Metal\\*\\*: remove jewellery, hairpins, hearing aids, wallets\n### Prerequisites: Creatinine if Contrast Planned\n- Bring recent kidney function report or test at our lab in 5 minutes.\n### Best Time: Schedule According to Symptoms\n- Emergencies: same-day slot\n- Routine: morning slots for diabetic patients\n### Eligibility: Pacemaker, Pregnancy Checks\n- Fill safety form; pregnancy test for women of child-bearing age\n- Pacemaker? Bring device card for MRI compatibility verification.\n---\n## Procedure for Taking an MRI Brain + Orbits\n1. \\*\\*Check-in\\*\\*: verify ID, safety checklist, change to gown.\n2. \\*\\*IV line\\*\\* (if contrast): placed by nurse.\n3. \\*\\*Positioning\\*\\*: lie on back, head in cushioned coil.\n4. \\*\\*Earplugs & headphones\\*\\*: music of your choice.\n5. \\*\\*Scanning\\*\\*: 5–7 sequences, 20–40 minutes total.\n6. \\*\\*Contrast injection\\*\\* midway if ordered; brief warm sensation.\n7. \\*\\*Completion\\*\\*: IV removed, post-procedure observation 10 min.\n---\n## Caution Before Taking the Test\n- \\*\\*Inform staff\\*\\* about implants, tattoos, or prior contrast allergy.\n- \\*\\*Sedation options\\*\\*: 5 mg diazepam oral tablet 30 min prior (driver required).\n- \\*\\*Allergy history\\*\\*: alternative contrast agents or pre-medication available."
